The main periods of the development of Russian culture from the 9th till the end of the 19th century are discussed, the reflection of the same events and facts in the various types of sources are compared, and transformation of the historical facts in literary texts is analyzed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To put in touch with the main periods of the development of Russian culture, the connection between the philology and history, the importance of the criticism of the sources (texts), the need of reflection on the positions of the researchers. To lay the groundwork for study of history of Russian literature, to analyze the transformation of the discourse in the various types of historical narration, and to develop abilities of producing papers and abstracts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student  1)	knows the main periods of the development of Russian culture 2)	 conceives of the main sources and concepts of the history of Russian culture 3)	understands the difference between the scientific and literature approach to history 4)	receives the first experience of referring research papers 5)	composes a correctly formatted essay
